last_episode_to_air.name: Rocket Jo needs that helmet
last_episode_to_air.overview: The jet pack takes off without Rocket Jo! He stares up at the sky, a dazed look on his face. A few seconds later, various pieces of the dismantled jet pack start raining down, one by one – the engine, then the turbine blades, next the reactor, then the steering levers. RJ deftly dodges these falling projectiles, which wind up sticking out of the ground. Proud of his dexterity, he starts tooting his own horn. Then, all of a sudden, the heftiest part of the jet pack – the refrigerator – comes plummeting down on top of him! Rocket Jo leaps feverishly out of the door, then lumbers a few feet, before finally crumpling in a heap of defeat!

name: Rocket Jo
overview: In the city of Ultrapolis, informed by his fellow pigeons, Randolf is fighting swindlers and crime. He transforms into a mysterious, comical and lovable hero named Pigeon Boy. He may be more Charlie Chaplin than Batman or Superman but he does his best to catch criminal...
